<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="50" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1886,2028]" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">
Published by Levichev in 
<bibRefCitation author="Peterson, A. &amp; Levichev, I. G. &amp; Peterson, J." box="[472,740,1886,1912]" pageId="6" pageNumber="50" pagination="446 - 465" refId="ref10393" refString="Peterson, A., Levichev, I. G. &amp; Peterson, J. (2008) Systematics of Gagea and Lloydia (Liliaceae) and infrageneric classification of Gagea based on molecular and morphological data. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 46: 446 - 465." type="journal article" year="2008">
Peterson 
<emphasis box="[586,648,1887,1912]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">et al.</emphasis>
(2008)
</bibRefCitation>
, this section has only one species, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hayne) Salisbury (1806: 556)" authorityName="Salisbury" authorityPageNumber="556" authorityYear="1806" baseAuthorityName="Hayne" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="6" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spathacea">
<emphasis box="[1171,1328,1887,1912]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">G. spathacea</emphasis>
(Hayne) 
<bibRefCitation author="Salisbury, R. A." box="[151,412,1925,1951]" pageId="6" pageNumber="50" pagination="553 - 557" refId="ref10724" refString="Salisbury, R. A. (1806) On the characters of a distinct genus hitherto confounded with Ornithogalum, and called Gagea; with some remarks on the importance of the inflorescence in distinguishing genera. Annals of Botany 2: 553 - 557." type="journal article" year="1806">Salisbury (1806: 556)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Independent analyses by 
<bibRefCitation author="Peterson, A. &amp; Levichev, I. G. &amp; Peterson, J." box="[720,974,1925,1951]" pageId="6" pageNumber="50" pagination="446 - 465" refId="ref10393" refString="Peterson, A., Levichev, I. G. &amp; Peterson, J. (2008) Systematics of Gagea and Lloydia (Liliaceae) and infrageneric classification of Gagea based on molecular and morphological data. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 46: 446 - 465." type="journal article" year="2008">
Peterson 
<emphasis box="[829,888,1925,1950]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">et al.</emphasis>
(2008)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Zarrei, M. &amp; Wilkin, P. &amp; Fay, M. F. &amp; Ingrouille, M. J. &amp; Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W." box="[1033,1257,1925,1951]" pageId="6" pageNumber="50" pagination="125 - 142" refId="ref11349" refString="Zarrei, M., Wilkin, P., Fay, M. F., Ingrouille, M. J., Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W. (2009) Molecular systematics of Gagea and Lloydia (Liliaceae; Liliales): implications of analyses of nuclear ribosomal and plastid sequences for infrageneric classification. Annals of Botany 104: 125 - 142." type="journal article" year="2009">
Zarrei 
<emphasis box="[1112,1171,1925,1950]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">et al.</emphasis>
(2009)
</bibRefCitation>
do not support the section as distinct from other members of 
<emphasis box="[693,718,1964,1989]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">G.</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[786,957,1964,1989]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">Didymobulbos</emphasis>
. No anatomical or palynomorphological features were studied in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Salisbury" authorityYear="1806" baseAuthorityName="Hayne" box="[437,588,2003,2028]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="6" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spathacea">
<emphasis box="[437,588,2003,2028]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">G. spathacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but this section is not recognised here.
</paragraph>
